DISCLAIMER: There is no warranty of fitness for any purpose or support
provided by Wind River for rebuilt u-boot. You can rebuild the bootloader,
but you are responsible for the safety of your board and any issues that
the rebuilt u-boot causes.

1. Building u-boot:
==================
Using the following steps to build the u-boot:
  a) cd <your project dir>/build
  b) make virtual/bootloader

2. Rebuilding u-boot:
=====================
If you modify the u-boot source codes, run the following commands to
rebuild the u-boot:
  a) cd <your project dir>/build
  b) make bitbake-shell
  c) bitbake -f -c compile virtual/bootloader


